glam (0.10-3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Added thread locking to all text measuring.
  * GmTextWidget goes through the font manager to do text measuring.
  * Menu displays prettified.
  * Text positioning and label positioning updates for buttons.
  * TextPointSize changed to TextSize because size is in GL units.
  * Text offsets altered, offset refers to justification now.
  * GmPage default layout is set to list layout.
  * Various bug fixes.

 -- David Longley <dlongley@vt.edu>  Tue, 18 Nov 2003 20:12:37 -0500

glam (0.10-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Icon cache fixed so that svg renderers and texture ids are
    cached rather than GmIcons.
  * Table color bug fix.
  * relayout() call added
  * Action model changed so that object id's are included in actions.
  * Minor bug fixes.

 -- David Longley <dlongley@vt.edu>  Tue, 11 Nov 2003 19:31:56 -0500

glam (0.10-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Major work for labels so they do not overflow the components they are placed within.
  * Font manager work to reduce memory usage.
  * Converted all use of "char*"s to C++ "string"s
  * Overhaul of tool tip code in an effort to make rich tooltip areas
  * Added thread-safety code to font manager.
  * Added drag and drop support to architecture
  * Added GmTextField class to architecture
  * Huge speed improvements by selectively pushing the correct OpenGL attributes
  * Many fixes to scrollable pane to enable simultaneous addition/scrolling of area
  * Added OpenGL x and y coordinates to mouse event
  * Continuing improvements for extent calculation for objects
  * Slew of other small bug fixes

 -- Manu Sporny <msporny@zenmachine.org>  Thu, 16 Oct 2003 11:36:57 -0400

glam (0.9-3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Now multiple focus listeners can be used to listen to the focus actions of any 
    interactive widget.
  * GmContainer, GmMenu, GmExpandableListItem, picking, and focus architecture improvements and fixes.
  * New SVG icons, one used for infobox closure.
  * General updates, fixes, and optimizations.

 -- David Longley <dlongley@vt.edu>  Thu,  2 Oct 2003 14:44:52 -0400

glam (0.9-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * General updates, segfault fixes, and optimizations.
  * Keyboard events are now distributed in the same way mouse events are distributed.
  * Major updates and fixes to focus architecture (including new focus status types).
  * Preliminary keyboard handling implemented (tabbing through containers, focused 
    widgets receive keyboard events, menus can use spacebar for selection).
  * Added timestamps to events.
  * Changed all occurrences of Arial.ttf to Vera.ttf.

